Wed Sep 27 19:40:12 1995  Jonathan Kamens  <jik@annex-1-slip-jik.cam.ov.com>

	* XRn.src, patchlevel.h, xrn-man.src: Update version number for
 	7.04-beta-9.

Wed Sep 27 19:38:10 1995  Jonathan Kamens  <jik@annex-1-slip-jik.cam.ov.com>

 *	* internals.c (enterNewsgroup): Don't call groupSnapshotSave() or
 	change CurrentGroup when returning XRN_NOUNREAD when the
 	ENTER_UNREAD flag is set.  Before, groupSnapshotSave() was being
 	called and CurrentGroup was being set even when enterNewsgroup()
 	was returning an error to the caller.  This may have been causing
 	various subtle bugs that I don't know about, but the one I *do*
 	know about is that it was causing a temporary-file leak which is
 	now fixed.

	* internals.c, save.c, server.c, utils.h: Add debugging code for
 	temporary-file leaks.

	* config.h, utils.h: Use the tempnam() in the C library on Linux,
 	even if this does mean that there's no declaration for it in the
 	Linux header files.

	* config.h, utils.h: "#define utTempnam tempnam" belongs in
 	utils.h, not in config.h.

	* allMode.c (doAll): Detect when we have to redraw the entire
 	newsgroup list because we're changing a group to or from "ignored"
 	status, and the newsgroup list is displayed in Newsrc order, which
 	means that all of the ignored groups are displayed at the end.

	* cursor.c (currentMode): Use strncmp() instead of strmp() when
 	checking whether a group is currently subscribed, unsubscribed or
 	ignored, so that we won't get confused if it's not the last group
 	in the list.  I introduced this bug in revision 1.20 (i.e., in
 	release 7.01-beta-19); it's amazing that it hasn't been discovered
 	before now :-).

 *	* allMode.c (allMoveFunction): Fix a bug which was causing XRN to
	spin-dry (i.e., to go into an infinite loop) when the user
	attempted to move newsgroups in his .newsrc.

