 	pointed out by numerous people, the first of whom was "Ivar
 	Ruyter" <ivarr@troll.hz.kfa-juelich.de>.

 *	* internals.c (rescanWorkProc): Call doPrefetch() after fetching
 	new statistics about a group, if it's not the currently prefetched
 	group.  This way, if there were previously no unread articles (so
 	that no group was prefetched) and then we discover a group with
 	unread articles, it is prefetched immediately.

Sun Sep 24 13:19:07 1995  Jonathan Kamens  <jik@annex-1-slip-jik.cam.ov.com>

	* XRn.src, patchlevel.h, xrn-man.src: Update version number for
 	7.04-beta-7.

Sun Sep 24 13:07:15 1995  Jonathan Kamens  <jik@annex-1-slip-jik.cam.ov.com>

	* internals.c (articleIsAvailable): If we've already got a file
 	for an article, then assume that the article is available without
 	checking if its Subject can be retrieved from the server.  This
	should prevent a small amount of unnecessary traffic with the
	server.

 *	* artstruct.c (freeartstruct): Unlink temporary files when freeing
 	article structures.  I believe this fixes a temporary-file leak
	(i.e., I believe it prevents XRN from leaving some files in /tmp
	when it exits).

 *	* addMode.c, internals.c, internals.h: Fix bug reported by
 	Jean-Marc.Lasgouttes@inria.fr (Jean-Marc Lasgouttes): "When new
 	newsgroups appear, xrn presents them to me at each rescan, until I
 	leave the program to update .newsrc (or the cache perhaps). This
 	with fullNewsrc set to false, if it makes a difference."

	* internals.c (setUpGroupIncremental): Don't call
 	setCurrentArticle() until we're actually done processing the KILL
 	file.  This prevents a small amount of unnecessary traffic with
	the server.

	* activecache.c, cache.h (new file), varfile.c: Use #define's to
 	represent the prefixes for the lines in the cache file, instead of
 	hard-coding them.

	* server.c (check_server_response): Don't call getactive().

	* allMode.c, artMode.c, mesg_strings.c, ngMode.c: Convert
 	UNKNOWN_ENTER_NG_RESPONSE_MSG to more generic
 	UNKNOWN_FUNC_RESPONSE_MSG.

	* mesg_strings.c: Delete UNKNOWN_FIND_UNRD_RESPONSE_MSG, which is
 	no longer used.

 *	* Imakefile, XRn.src, activecache.c (new file), activecache.h (new
 	file), butexpl.h, internals.c, internals.h, mesg_strings.c,
 	newsrc.y, newsrcfile.c, newsrcfile.h, ngMode.c, ngMode.h,
 	resources.c, resources.h, server.c, server.h, xrn-man.src: Added
 	the new "cacheActive" resource and the "ngGetList" command in
 	newsgroup mode.  When "cacheActive" is set to True (by default, it
 	is False), XRN will cache the server's newsgroup list so that it
 	doesn't have to retrieve the whole list every time it starts up
 	and every time it does a "Rescan", and the "Rescan" command does
 	the rescan group-by-group instead of retrieving a full list, and
 	it does the rescan in the background so you can do other things
 	(such as reading the articles in a group that has already been
 	rescanned) while it's going on.

	This new functionality will probably be used most frequently by
	people reading news over a SLIP or PPP link who don't want to
	download a complete newsgroup list every time they check for new
	articles.

	Note that the first time you run XRN with "cacheActive" enabled,
	it will have to retrieve a full newsgroup list in order to prime
	the cache.

