Tue Sep  5 18:57:22 1995  Jonathan Kamens  <jik@annex-1-slip-jik.cam.ov.com>

 *	* compose.c, compose.h, mesg_strings.c, ngMode.c: Don't let the
 	user quit or exit from the program if a composition is pending.

	* artMode.c: If killing an author instead of a subject, then the
 	message displayed after killing should say "Author has been
 	killed" instead of "Subject has been killed".

	* server.c (getlineslist): Don't retrieve anything if
 	displayLineCount is false.

	* xthelper.c, xthelper.h: Add support in xthWaitForMapped for
 	waiting for an expose event too.

	* xthelper.c: Add some debugging support to
 	xthHandleAllPendingEvents.

	* xrn.c: xthWaitForMapped() now has an extra argument to specify
 	whether an expose event should also be waited for.  We're not
 	using that functionality here, but we still need to specify False
 	as the new argument.

	* internals.c, internals.h: Make it possible for fillUpArray() to
 	be aborted part-way through.

	* cursor.c: fillUpArray() now has another argument and a return
 	value, because it can be told to allow an abort in the middle of
 	its work.  We're not using that functionality here, but we still
 	need to account for the new argument.

 *	* cancel.c: When creating a cancel button, wait until it's mapped
 	and gets an expose event, and then process all pending events so
 	that its label will be drawn properly, before returning.  This
 	way, cancel buttons will be popped up and drawn when they're
 	supposed to be instead of being delayed.

 *	* artMode.c: Add a cancel button to "List Old" in article mode.
  	This was suggested by George Ross <gdmr@dcs.ed.ac.uk>.
  	Unfortunately, it's not possible to do this really well without
 	significantly slowing down the performance of the "List Old"
 	command, at least not until the program is multi-threaded or talks
 	to the NNTP server in a sub-process or something like that.  With
 	this change, the "List Old" can be aborted either one-third of the
 	way through the work it does or two-thirds of the way through.
  	It's not very good granularity, but it's better than nothing.

	* resources.c: Alphabetize the options in the usage message, and
 	delete one redundant one.

